22:09.722 --> 22:11.424
I show 0500.

22:11.524 --> 22:15.944
Show up a little earlier,
I'll make you French toast.

22:23.565 --> 22:25.533
Every marine out of those
racks and on my deck.

22:25.633 --> 22:27.001
Get your ass up.

22:27.101 --> 22:28.702
You've got five seconds.

22:28.802 --> 22:31.171
Five seconds.
Up up.

22:31.271 --> 22:33.072
Let's go.
- Move your ass.

22:33.172 --> 22:35.941
Get up. Move.

22:36.041 --> 22:38.410
Don't you eyeball me.
You stand at attention.

22:38.510 --> 22:40.612
And how come we're the only
ones running like this?

22:40.712 --> 22:43.147
Every damn morning.
- To make us the best.

22:43.247 --> 22:45.883
Oh, shut up.
I'm so sick of this shit.

22:45.983 --> 22:49.723
I just want to get out there and slap a Jap.

22:53.591 --> 22:55.159
What did you say?

22:55.259 --> 22:58.761
I said I want to slap a Jap, gunny.

23:03.365 --> 23:05.398
'slap a Jap'?

23:06.733 --> 23:08.238
Well, how about it, boys?

23:08.338 --> 23:11.174
I bet you all want
to do more than slap a Jap.

23:11.274 --> 23:14.061
Yes, gunny.

23:14.161 --> 23:16.212
'Slap a Jap. '

23:20.387 --> 23:23.532
That's what the enemy is to you, huh?

23:23.958 --> 23:26.492
A fucking bucktoothed cartoon dreamed up

23:26.592 --> 23:30.502
by some asshole on Madison
Avenue to sell soap.

23:30.961 --> 23:32.730
Well, let me tell you something.

23:32.830 --> 23:35.298
The Jap I know,

23:35.398 --> 23:37.834
The Japanese soldier,

23:37.934 --> 23:39.934
He has been at war

23:40.003 --> 23:43.540
Since you were in fucking diapers.

23:43.640 --> 23:45.042
He's a combat veteran,

23:45.142 --> 23:47.377
An expert with his weapon.

23:47.477 --> 23:50.213
He can live off of maggoty rice

23:50.313 --> 23:52.882
And muddy water for weeks and endure misery

23:52.982 --> 23:56.807
You couldn't dream up
in your worst nightmare.

23:57.886 --> 24:00.855
The Japanese soldier doesn't
care if he gets hurt or killed,

24:00.955 --> 24:03.723
As long as he kills you.

24:04.992 --> 24:07.460
Now you can call them whatever you want,

24:07.560 --> 24:11.196
But never, ever fail

24:11.296 --> 24:15.900
To respect their desire to put you
and buddies into an early grave.

24:16.000 --> 24:19.236
Is that clear?
- Yes, gunny.

24:19.336 --> 24:21.170
Why aren't you in your full packs?

24:21.270 --> 24:22.705
Gear up.

24:22.805 --> 24:26.542
10-mile run in formation

24:26.642 --> 24:29.610
In two minutes.

24:52.963 --> 24:55.003
You're gonna enjoy this.

24:56.534 --> 24:58.534
Almost ready.

25:04.641 --> 25:06.443
Pretty fancy for 0500.

25:06.543 --> 25:10.280
You strike me as an Italian mama's boy,

25:10.380 --> 25:13.749
Worshipped and pampered
just like my brothers.

25:13.849 --> 25:16.383
I wanted to make you feel at home.

25:16.483 --> 25:19.652
Well... I was told

25:19.752 --> 25:21.487
At a very early age I was the best thing

25:21.587 --> 25:24.456
Since sliced capicola.

25:24.556 --> 25:26.525
And there's enough for seconds.

25:26.625 --> 25:28.493
You'll want seconds.
- This is good.

25:28.593 --> 25:31.762
When I first got
here, the coffee was dreadful.

25:31.862 --> 25:34.431
How a marine mess can serve
bad coffee is beyond me.

25:34.531 --> 25:36.600
I can't live without it.

25:36.700 --> 25:39.970
The best coffee I ever
had was on Guadalcanal

25:40.070 --> 25:41.738
The morning after the battle.

25:41.838 --> 25:44.643
I know the story.
- Not this part.

25:45.274 --> 25:48.010
We stole some coffee from the
doggies when they came ashore.

25:48.110 --> 25:50.111
Liberated some hooch
from their officers too.

25:50.211 --> 25:52.847
Anyway, the morning after the battle,

25:52.947 --> 25:55.983
My guys cooked up the coffee over
a fire of green coconut logs.

25:56.083 --> 25:58.118
There wasn't any part
of me that didn't hurt-

25:58.218 --> 26:00.586
Burns on my hands,

26:01.654 --> 26:04.799
Ears still ringing from the shelling.

26:05.458 --> 26:08.660
But when they handed me that cup of coffee,

26:08.760 --> 26:10.728
I never tasted anything so good.

26:10.828 --> 26:13.633
Not that I don't appreciate this.

26:15.399 --> 26:19.139
What was the best cup
of coffee you ever had?

26:20.738 --> 26:24.241
My parents were real traditional.

26:24.341 --> 26:28.043
I was supposed to get married
and give them grandkids.

26:28.143 --> 26:31.711
So when I announced
that I'd joined the marines,

26:31.811 --> 26:34.146
There was a lot of yelling and crying

26:34.246 --> 26:38.015
And finally my father
just stopped talking to me,

26:38.115 --> 26:41.618
Cut me out of t family.

26:41.718 --> 26:45.421
A year later I got my stripes.
I went home to see my mom, my brothers.

26:45.521 --> 26:48.489
I was sitting in this diner

26:48.589 --> 26:49.991
And my pop walked in,

26:50.091 --> 26:53.999
Sat down beside me.
He ordered two cups of coffee

26:54.099 --> 26:58.435
And he put the milk and one sugar in for me.

27:00.338 --> 27:02.803
That was the best I ever had.

27:07.044 --> 27:11.464
It's incredible what can
happen over a cup of coffee.

27:15.818 --> 27:18.113
My enlistment's up in July.

27:19.922 --> 27:21.890
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

27:21.990 --> 27:26.580
You're gonna take a discharge
and you're gonna go home.

27:28.463 --> 27:30.898
I should be looking forward to my freedom,

27:30.998 --> 27:33.801
But I can't imagine it.

27:33.901 --> 27:35.902
I love the marines.

27:36.002 --> 27:39.605
You do too.
I love everything about it.

27:39.705 --> 27:44.210
I can't imagine being anywhere
or doing anything else.

27:48.847 --> 27:51.381
Lena.
- Yeah?

27:53.451 --> 27:55.552
You might hear this all the time,

27:55.652 --> 27:59.902
But you're the most beautiful
woman I've ever seen.

28:03.392 --> 28:05.392
